questions.q:
The quadratic equation whose roots are $l$ and $m$, where
$$
\begin{aligned}
&amp; l=\lim _{\theta \rightarrow 0}\left(\frac{3 \sin \theta-4 \sin ^2 \theta}{\theta}\right), \\
&amp; m=\lim _{\theta \rightarrow 0} \frac{2 \tan \theta}{\theta\left(1-\tan ^2 \theta\right)}, \text { is }
\end{aligned}
$$

questions.solution:
Let $\alpha, \beta, \gamma$ are roots of equation
$$
\begin{aligned}
&amp; x^3+a x^2+b x+c=0 \\
&amp; \alpha+\beta+\gamma=-a \\
&amp; \therefore \quad \alpha \beta+\beta \gamma+\gamma \alpha=b \\
&amp; \text { Now, } \alpha^{-1}+\beta^{-1}+\gamma^{-1}=\frac{1}{\alpha}+\frac{1}{\beta}+\frac{1}{\gamma} \\
&amp;=\frac{\alpha \beta+\beta \gamma+\gamma \alpha}{\alpha \beta \gamma}=\frac{b}{-c}=-\frac{b}{c}
\end{aligned}
$$
